				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$FB{C}_{i=1}^{n(CCS)}(B=A,C,G,T)=\frac{n({B}_{i})}{n({A}_{i})+n({C}_{i})+n({G}_{i})+n({T}_{i})}$$\end{document}FBCi=1n(CCS)(B=A,C,G,T)=n(Bi)n(Ai)+n(Ci)+n(Gi)+n(Ti)where n(Bi) is the number of occurrences of base B in CCS i and n(CCS) is the number of CCS with acceptable quality spanning the SSR. Once the vector elements were computed, the absolute value of the FBC z-score threshold was iteratively adjusted, usually from larger to smaller values, to identify and remove CCS exceeding the FBC threshold for each base.
